      {name: "Amy Wadge", biog: "Amy Wadge, originally from Bristol and now based in South Wales, is an established singer/songwriter on the acousic scene.  She won ‘Best Female Artist’ at the Welsh Music Awards two years running beating Charlotte Church and Cerys Matthews.  Amy has released 4 studio albums to critical acclaim and has toured extensively through out the UK, Europe, South East Asia, America and Australia.  <br /><br />Amy has opened for Van Morrison, Lenny Kravitz,  The Stereophonics, Eric Bibb and toured with Jeff Beck on his first tour in 15 years which included two nights at the Albert Hall.  Prior to writing songs for Ed Sheeran, Amy has been an established writer for other artists and has worked with Marti Pellow, Amy Nuttel, Chris Difford, Jade Gallagher, Lucinda Belle, Henry Priestman (The Christians) and Pete Riley. <br /><br />In 2009, we changed Amy’s life and introduced her to a very young Ed Sheeran, they wrote the EP, ‘Songs I Wrote With Amy’ [Atlantic Records] and ‘GoldRush’ which features on Ed’s 6 x platinum Deluxe Edition album +. After his major Worldwide success, Amy continues to work with Ed and is now enjoying his forthcoming successes of 2 songs which they wrote together, the No.1 worldside hit, ‘Thinking Out Loud’ and ‘Even Dad Says Sometimes’ which both feature on Ed’s new album, X [Asylum - Atlantic Records].  Other recent collaborations; Leann Rimes, Keith Urban, Matt Woods [unsigned], Ryan Ashley [PMR Records], Shannon Saunders [Caroline Records], Lewis Watson [Warner records], Martin Garrix [Virgin-EMI records].", links: "", photo_file_name: "amy.jpg", photo_content_type: "image/jpeg", photo_file_size: 186079, photo_updated_at: "2015-03-30 12:07:29", twitter: "twitter.com", facebook: "facebook.com", composer: true, songwriter: false},
      {name: "Test", biog: "", links: "", photo_file_name: "cover170x170_(4).jpeg", photo_content_type: "image/jpeg", photo_file_size: 21272, photo_updated_at: "2015-04-16 13:14:15", twitter: "", facebook: "", composer: false, songwriter: false},
      {name: "Test", biog: "", links: "", photo_file_name: "cover170x170_(4).jpeg", photo_content_type: "image/jpeg", photo_file_size: 21272, photo_updated_at: "2015-04-16 13:14:26", twitter: "", facebook: "", composer: false, songwriter: false},
      {name: "Jake Gosling", biog: "Jake Gosling is a Brit Award and MPG Award nominated Producer of The Year [2013] Multi-Platinum Selling Music Producer/Songwriter/Remixer and manager best known for his work with artists such as Wiley, Paloma Faith, One Direction and Ed Sheeran. Jake runs his own studio, Sticky Studios, in Surrey. He is signed to BDi Music alongside his co-venture publishing company, The Movement, which was established in 2009 with co-founder, Sarah Liversedge [Managing Director and owner of BDi Music]. The Movement nurtures and develops breaking urban producers and writers within the music industry.\u2028<br /><br />Jake started playing in bands at college and usually ended up producing the bands he was in so it made complete sense to make it his full-time profession. Jake is multi talented - he has been lead singer in many bands and also plays keys, drums, accordion, melodian and percussion but, making ‘beats’ and playing with samples is what he does best. Jake likes to use a mix of analogue with digital, mixing old sounds with new technologies, by ripping up vinyl, sampling and creating his own unique sound. It is important to him that the ‘vibe’ is strong and he has a great understanding of how to work with up-and-coming artists and established professionals.\u2028Jake has an extensive back-catalogue of hit songs ranging from Pop and Singer-Songwriter ballads through to Grime and R&B/Urban tracks. Since 2009, he has immersed himself in the urban scene and has become a pivotal producer and songwriter in this genre. He has co-written and produced with the God of Grime, Wiley and he has played an integral role in developing new artists such as Scorcher, Mikall Pane, Jelluzz and Fugative. Jake has also produced official remixes for Lady Gaga, Timbaland, Keri Hilson and Nelly Furtado under his remixer pseudonym, Sketch Iz Dead. Between 2009 - 2011, his attention was mostly focussed on the truly brilliant, Ed Sheeran. \u2028<br /><br />Jake is now well known for being Ed Sheeran’s right hand man, record producer. Sarah Liversedge introduced Jake to Ed and from that point onwards they were a match made in heaven. Their first independent success arrived in early 2011 with ‘The No 5 Collaborations Project’ which featured urban artists: Wiley, Wretch 32, P Money, JME, Dot Rotten and Devlin. This ground breaking EP/Album reached number 2 on the iTunes album chart within its first day of release challenging no other than Rihanna for top spot! Jake was producer and co-writer on this project. Following the success of \"The No 5 Collaborations project\", Jake was snapped up by Asylum Records, a subsidary of Atlantic Records, to produce and co-write on Ed’s debut 5 times platinum album \"+\". It charted at No.1 in the Official UK Album Chart in September 2011, going gold in October 2011 and the first single from the platinum selling album, \"The A Team\", went straight in at No.3 in the UK singles chart - ‘The A Team’ which is also now platinum status and in the USA hit No.10 in the billboard charts. He has been named Music Week’s No.1 Top Producer 0f 2012. He also produced ‘Moment’ and ‘Little Things’ for One Direction’s top selling album ‘Take Me Home’ - ‘Little Things’ reached No.1 in the UK Charts - the album has been No.1 in over 20 countries.\u2028Jake has attended many songwriter camps around the world in conjunction with his publishers, BDi Music, Bucks Music Group and the major record labels.\u2028<br /><br /> In 2012 Jake completed work on the soundtrack to a new British feature film \"Twenty8K\" in collaboration with British film composer, Ruth Barrett, also published by BDi Music. The film is produced by Formosa Films in association with legendary screen writer, Paul Abbott was released in UK on 1st October 2012. \u2028<br /><br />Jake has drawn from his strong contacts within the UK urban music scene, to bring artists such as Ghettz, Roxxxan, Smiler, Random Impulse and Mikill Pane into the film. Jake just finished producing the single b side and album track for One Direction. His recent writing collaborations include Ed Sheeran [Warners], Professor Green [Virgin], Yelawolf [signed to Eminem’s Shady Records] and Paloma Faith [Sony]. In 2013 Jake produced and co-wrote albums for Mikill Pane, ‘Blame It On Miss Barclay’ [Mercury Records] and Nina Nesbitt, ‘Peroxide’ [Island Records]. Later end of 2013 he produced USA artist, Christina Perri’s single and album. 2014 has seen the return of Ed Sheeran – Jake produced 7 tracks on the NO.1 album, X [UK/USA and 65 other countries WW]. ‘Lego House’ has now sold over 1 million copies.\u2028\u2028\u2028\u2028\u2028", links: "", photo_file_name: "jake.jpg", photo_content_type: "image/jpeg", photo_file_size: 164806, photo_updated_at: "2015-03-30 12:06:45", twitter: "twitter.com", facebook: "facebook.com", composer: true, songwriter: true}
    ])
