    Staff.create!([
      {name: "Sarah Liversedge", biog: "Sarah Liversedge is co-founder and Managing Director of the award winning and independent UK music publishing company, BDi Music, a sister company to Bucks Music Group.<br  /><br />\r\n \r\nSarah studied music composition at Bath Spa University acquiring a First Class BA Honours degree. Sarah’s TV media career kicked off as a Floor Manager for UK Television. She then side-stepped into a TV Researcher role for BBC TV and after only a few  years in this position was promoted to Programme Liaison Executive for BBCWW Music, the commercial arm of the BBC. In 2000, Sarah was appointed Deputy Head of Music Publishing at BBC WW Music and Head of Music in 2004. In this role, Sarah played a major part in developing and expanding what became a multimillion pound business and one of the leading media music publishing companies in the UK. <br  /><br />\r\n\r\nBDi Music was founded in 2004, since inception BDi has been awarded 2 Ivor Novello Awards, 3 RTS Awards, 1 Bafta and 1 ASCAP Award in 2014. BDi is proud to be co-publisher of Ed Sheeran’s triple platinum No.1 album, +, produced and co-written by Jake Gosling, and co-publisher of Ed’s top ten singles, ‘Lego House’, ‘Drunk’ and ‘Give Me Love’. This year has seen further success with Amy Wadge co-writing Ed Sheeran’s No.1 single, ‘Thinking Out Loud’, produced by Jake Gosling. Jake has 7 produced tracks on X and Amy has 2 co-writes.<br  /><br />\r\n\r\nSarah is co-founder of The Movement, an organisation which nurtures and develops unbeatable, innovative and creative forces of young and talented producers and songwriters: http://www.themovement.uk.com.  Sarah has been a member of the MPA’s Pop Publisher’s Committee for the last 3 years and she is an industry adviser on the PRS Foundation Momentum Fund. Sarah was also nominated in 2013 for an Music Producer’s Guild Award, Unsung Hero, category.<br  /><br />\r\n\r\nSarah’s extensive experience within the music and media industry has provided her with strong relations in Film, TV and Radio production companies and with producers, directors, agents, managers, publishers, record labels, media composers and songwriters. This year, Sarah was honoured with outstanding contribution to the music industry as part of Women in Music 2014. ", photo_file_name: "1924201_47097778975_6122_n.jpg", photo_content_type: "image/jpeg", photo_file_size: 72965, photo_updated_at: "2015-03-30 12:02:21", role: "Managing Director", email: "sarah@bdimusic.com", phone: "0207 243 4101"},
      {name: "Simon Platz", biog: "Simon Platz is Managing Director of Bucks Music Group Ltd and has 20 years of experience in international music publishing. Simon joined the family firm of Essex Music in 1984. Essex was founded by Howie Richmond (US) and Simon’s father David in the 1950’s. The Essex catalogue of titles by the Rolling Stone, David Bowie, Marc Bolan and Joe Cocker form the backbone to Bucks Music Group’s current operation. Essex was demerged soon after Simon joined and Bucks Music became the Platz company moving forward. Bucks Music now has wholly owned companies throughout the world and has a varied roster of composers covering all types of music genre from Drum and Bass to Jazz, and Media music. Bucks’ recent Ivor Novello successes include: Beautiful Liar by Amanda Ghost & Beyonce; You’re Beautiful by Amanda Ghost, Sacha Skarbek & James Blunt; and Elizabeth by Rob Lane.<br /><br />\r\nSimon expanded the Bucks business specifically in the areas of television and film music rights. Simon is a founding member of the PRS Media committee, he is on the board of the Music Publishers Association and he is a board Director for both PRS and MCPS.", photo_file_name: "283900c1-12a0-4370-a4d9-5a4492faeb02-2.jpg", photo_content_type: "image/jpeg", photo_file_size: 28256, photo_updated_at: "2015-03-30 12:03:24", role: "Co-Director", email: "simon@bdimusic.com", phone: "0207 243 4101"},
      {name: "Henry Prince", biog: "Having spent the first 18 years of his life growing up in an English household in the south of France, learning to play various instruments and majoring in music at school, Henry then moved to London with a French baccalaureate  in 2007 to study Commercial Music Performance at the University of Westminster.<br /><br />\r\nThree years and a bachelor of music later Henry left university in search of work. He co-ran Sweet Beans Music Promotions specializing in  live cinematic bands, toured with bands and generally got involved with many pro bono ventures. Following this he became a part time events tech and part time project manager for Music Jobs France- the French arm of UK music industry networking and job search site UK Music Jobs, all the while pursuing his own projects on the side. <br /><br />\r\nIn Late 2011, he left Europe for India and Sri Lanka for 6 months to travel while his career had yet to really take off, after which he worked in a restaurant in Nice over the summer of 2012, gearing up to move back to London permanently. <br /><br />\r\nFinally, garnering new aspirations to work in music publishing and after a chance meeting with Sarah Liversedge, he became her Creative PA for BDi Music and Bucks Music Group. The rest is history.", photo_file_name: "cover170x170-47.jpeg", photo_content_type: "image/jpeg", photo_file_size: 10232, photo_updated_at: "2015-03-30 12:02:56", role: "Creative PA to Sarah Liversedge ", email: "henry@bdimusic.com", phone: "0207 221 4275"}
    ])
